                <foliation/>
                <collation>
                  <p>The quires, signed with letters, were originally 30 in number.</p>
                </collation>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Some leaves are much torn, especially foll. <locus from="1" to="2">1, 2</locus>, <locus from="8" to="8">8</locus>, <locus from="10" to="10">10</locus>, <locus from="23" to="24">23, 24</locus>, <locus from="26" to="26">26</locus>, <locus from="115" to="115">115</locus>, <locus from="262" to="263">262, 263</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p>Of the quires, the first (with the exception of a single leaf), the second, and the last, are now missing.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p>Leaves are also wanting after foll. <locus from="2" to="2">2</locus>, <locus from="8" to="8">8</locus>, <locus from="22" to="22">22</locus>, <locus from="23" to="23">23</locus>, and <locus from="260" to="260">260</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="21 27">
                  <p>There are from 21 to 27 lines on each page.</p>
                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="4">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                <desc>This volume is written in a good, regular hand of the <origDate notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">13th century</origDate>. <ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref></desc>
              </handNote>
