            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc/>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                  <p>Some Syriac vowels have been added by the scribe</p>                  
                </item>
                <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                  <p>Other hands have inserted numerous Greek vowels, as well as the points rukkākh and kushshāi, both in red and black ink.</p>
                </item>
                <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                  <p>There are also many marginal notes and glosses, chiefly in Arabic, by different hands</p>
                </item>
                <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                  <p>A few lessons (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܩܪ̈ܝܢܐ</foreign>) have been marked on the margins; e.g. foll. <locus from="40b" to="40b">40 b</locus>, <locus from="41b" to="41b">41 b</locus>, and <locus from="44b" to="44b">44 b</locus>.</p>
                </item>
              </list>
